  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nBecause there is no way to serialize the task instance.\r\n\r\nI think that we should:\r\n\r\n1. Add a `setTask()` variant that accepts `Class<Consumer<ScheduledExecution>> consumerClass` instead (and the same for `setAsyncTask()` of course),\r\n2. Fail the registration if `JobDefinition#setTask(Consumer<ScheduledExecution>)` is called and `quarkus-quartz` and DB type store is used,\r\n3. Either make it clear that `Scheduler.unscheduleJob()`, `Scheduler.getScheduledJob()` and `Scheduler.getScheduledJobs()` will not reflect the jobs registered programmatically after the app restart or try to fix this part as well.\r\n\r\n### Workaround \r\n\r\nDelete the job manually with `org.quartz.Scheduler.deleteJob(JobKey)` and `new JobKey(\"THE_JOB_IDENTITY\", \"io.quarkus.scheduler.Scheduler\")` and reschedule it.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe `JobDefinition` programmatic API works if `quarkus-quartz` and DB type store is used.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
